The paper focuses on developing a real-time state estimation system for a robotic application, specifically inserting an object into a tight space using suction cups. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed framework fuses force and visual sensing, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The algorithm also incorporates kinematic measurements from the robot, which involves control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.SY.
